    main.c-Document.c-Document--Draft
      header
        h1 Evaluation Portfolio
        p.o-Box.c-Alert.c-Alert--dang This document is a work in progress.
      section
        h2 Professional Knowledge
        p.
          Teachers of mathematics demonstrate an understanding of the curriculum, subject content,
          and the developmental needs of students by providing relevant learning experiences.
      section
        h2 Instructional Planning
        p.
          Teachers of mathematics plan using the Virginia Standards of Learning, the school&rsquo;s
          curriculum, effective strategies, resources, and data to meet the needs of all students.
      section
        h2 Instructional Delivery
        p.
          Teachers of mathematics effectively engage students in learning by using a variety of
          instructional strategies in order to meet individual learning needs.
      section
        h2 Assessment of and for Student Learning
        p.
          Teachers of mathematics systematically gather, analyze, and use all relevant data
          to measure student academic progress, guide instructional content and delivery methods,
          and provide timely feedback to both students and parents throughout the school year.
      section
        h2 Learning Environment
        p.
          Teachers of mathematics use resources, routines, and procedures to provide a respectful,
          positive, safe student-centered environment that is conducive to learning.
      section
        h2 Professionalism
        p.
          Teachers of mathematics maintain a commitment to professional ethics, communicate
          effectively, take responsibility for and participate in professional growth that
          results in enhanced student learning.
